HEADWORD: Latinization
<hw>Lat`in*i*za"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act or
process of Latinizing, as a word, language, or country.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The Germanization of Britain went far deeper than the
<qex>Latinization</qex> of France.</q> <rj><qau>M.
Arnold.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Latinize</ent>⟦br⟧
